<TITLE> Nine get life for 2005 Barguna bomb blasts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barguna, March 12 (bdnews24.com) Nine people were sentenced to life imprisonment Wednesday in connection with the 2005 bomb blasts in Barguna, by the court of additional district judge Shahjahan Majumder. The convicted are Asadul Islam Arif, Hafiz Al Amin, Hafiz Mostafa Hasan and Shahidul Islam of Barguna upazila, Masum Billah, Rezaul Karim, Abdul Haq Abbasi and Abdur Rahman of Patharghata upazila and Shahidul Islam, known as Boxer Shahid, of Khulna. Of the nine convicted, six were present in court during the sentencing. The other three, Boxer Shahid, Abbasi and Abdur Rahman, are fugitive. On 17 Aug, 2005, Jamaatul Mujahideen Bangladesh carried out a series of simultaneous bomb blasts across Bangladesh, which included seven bombs set off in the Barguna district administrator's office, judge's court, press club and the local market. A charge sheet was filed on Dec 22, 2005, against twelve people in the case. The names of the other three accused were dropped after they were sentenced to death in a separate case. Militant leader Shayek Abdur Rahman, Siddiqul Islam, aka Bangla Bhai, and Ataur Rahman Sunny were dropped from the case on March 3, 2007, after they received the death sentence for the murder of a judge in Jhalkathi. bdnews
